HEADWORD: Priesthood
<hw>Priest"hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
office or character of a priest; the priestly function.</def>
<rj><au>Bk. of Com. Prayer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Priests, taken collectively; the order of men set
apart for sacred offices; the order of priests.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Priesting</ent>⟦br⟧
